    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q1">
      <label>1. What are the Essential Newborn Care services?</label>
      <item>
        <label>To dry the baby</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>To tie and cut the umbilical cord and use 7.1% Chlorhexidine on it</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Provide skin-to-skin care and keep the baby warm</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Start breast feeding within 1 hour of birth</label>
        <value>4</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q2">
      <label>2. How long should you provide skin-to-skin care to the baby?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Up to at least 4 hours after birth</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Up to at least 3 hours after birth</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Up to at least 2 hours after birth</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q3">
      <label>3. How long after birth should the baby initiate breastfeeding?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Within 1 hour of birth</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Within 2 hours of birth</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Within 3 hours of birth</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q4">
      <label>4. When should you use 7.1% Chlorhexidine?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Just after cutting the cord</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>72 hours after birth</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Never</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select appearance="rearrange_four" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q5">
      <label>5. How will you apply 7.1% Chlorhexidine on the cut cord?</label>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q5/1:label')"/>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q5/2:label')"/>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q5/3:label')"/>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q5/4:label')"/>
        <value>4</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q5/5:label')"/>
        <value>5</value>
      </item>
    </select>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q6">
      <label>6. What are the signs for a normal newborn baby?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Respiratory rate at 30-59/minute, Temperature at 38.5°C, Weight at 2500-4000g, Dry cord, Able to suck milk from the mother’s breast, Crying without any other symptoms, Can be easily woken up, Reduced movement, Temperature at 35.5°C – 37.5°C, Heart rate more than 160/minutes</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Weight at 2500-4000g, Dry cord, Able to suck milk from the mother’s breast, Crying without any other symptoms, Can be easily woken up, Reduced movement, Temperature at 35.5°C – 37.5°C, Heart rate more than 160/minutes</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>None of the above</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="compact" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q7">
      <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q7:label')"/>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q7/1:label')"/>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q7/2:label')"/>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q7/3:label')"/>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q8">
      <label>8. Why is it important to take the baby’s weight soon after birth?</label>
      <item>
        <label>To detect the babies who need special care</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>To let the mother and family know the baby’s weight</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>To determine how long the baby should breastfeed each time</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q9">
      <label>9. What is the correct position for breastfeeding?</label>
      <item>
        <label>The baby’s head and body will be in alignment</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>The baby’s nose will be positioned opposite the mother’s nipple</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>All of the above</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q10">
      <label>10. What are the signs of good attachment?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Nipple and more areola is inside the baby’s mouth</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Biting on the nipple and sucking the nipple hard</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Open the mouth wide</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q11">
      <label>11. Which of the following signs indicate that the baby is getting enough breast milk?</label>
      <item>
        <label>The baby will urinate 6-8 times a day and will sleep properly</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>The baby will keep crying continuously</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>The baby will be easily woken up from sleep</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q12">
      <label ref="jr:itext('/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q12:label')"/>
      <item>
        <label>Engorged breast, mastitis, flat nipples</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Cracked nipples</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>All of the above</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q13">
      <label>13. What are the causes of cracked nipple?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Having spicy food</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Wearing tight clothes</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Having poor attachment while breastfeeding</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q14">
      <label>14. What are the ways to prevent heat loss of the baby?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Keep the baby in skin-to-skin care</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Control the air flow inside the room</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Ensure that the baby is not in contact with anything wet or cold</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Ensure that the baby is not bathed within 72 hours of birth</label>
        <value>4</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>All of the above</label>
        <value>5</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q15">
      <label>15. What is the course of action to prevent the baby from having high temperature?</label>
      <item>
        <label>Ensure that the baby is not directly under the sun or near any other source of heat</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>If the baby is covered in excess clothing, take off the excess layers of clothing</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Cover the baby with more layers of clothes</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q16">
      <label>16. Within how many days after birth should all immunizations of the baby be completed?</label>
      <item>
        <label>10 months</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>12 months</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>15 months</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q17">
      <label>17. Where should you discard the used syringe after vaccination?</label>
      <item>
        <label>In a waste paper basket</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>In a safety box (for sharp objects)</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>None of the above</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
    </select1>
    <select appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q18">
      <label>18. Arrange the steps of measuring a baby’s weight in the correct order.</label>
      <item>
        <label>Wipe the weighing scale with a liquid antiseptic</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Put a clean cloth on top of the weighing scale</label>
        <value>2</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Bring the weighing scale to “0”</label>
        <value>3</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Take the baby’s clothes off and weigh the baby</label>
        <value>4</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <label>Record the weight of the baby</label>
        <value>5</value>
      </item>
    </select>
    <select1 appearance="button" ref="/chapter2_1_exam_en/c2_1_q19">
      <label>19. Which features would you use to classify the baby?</label>
      <item>
        <label>The baby’s weight, temperature and physical examination</label>
        <value>1</value>
      </item>
